byline.contributor: Christopher Cusack and Eli Rosenberg contributed reporting.
byline.original: By RICK ROJAS and NATE SCHWEBER

abstract: Police officials say they have found body of missing runner Karina Vetrano in Howard Beach neighborhood of Queens; investigators say they are reviewing surveillance footage and text messages from her phone, but have no leads on suspects.
lead_paragraph: Karina Vetrano, 30, had been reported missing by her family when she did not return from a jog in Spring Creek Park, near her home, the authorities said.

headline.main: Runner’s Body Is Found in Queens Marsh; Police Look for Answers
